<li id="cite_note-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">J.T. White (1897) "McCallum, Daniel Craig" in <i>The National Cyclopedia of American Biography</i>. p. 553</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-HAER_No._NY-332-35"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-HAER_No._NY-332_35-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HAER_No._NY-332_35-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://lcweb2.loc.gov/pnp/habshaer/ny/ny2000/ny2012/data/ny2012data.pdf">POWERSCOURT BRIDGE (Percy Bridge)</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140203100939/http://lcweb2.loc.gov/pnp/habshaer/ny/ny2000/ny2012/data/ny2012data.pdf">Archived</a> February 3, 2014, at the <a href="/wiki/Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine">Wayback Machine</a> Historic American Engineering Record HAER No. NY-332. National Park Service, U.S. Department of the Interior p. 5.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-36"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Poor's 1860 "History of the Railroad and Canals of the United States" is published in: <i><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=q08jAQAAMAAJ">Railway Locomotives and Cars</a></i>, Volume 33. (1860), for example, see p. 346</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-37"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Spencer C. Tucker (2013) <i>American Civil War: The Definitive Encyclopedia and Document Collection</i>. p. 1216</span>
</li>
